				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sigma =\frac{L}{A{R}_{m}}$$\end{document}where σ is the ionic conductivity of membranes in S cm−1, L is the membrane thickness in cm, A is the effective membrane area of 2.00 cm2, Rm is the membrane resistance in Ω. Rm is obtained by subtracting the resistance of the assembled coin cell with that of an otherwise-identical cell without any membrane.

